title: PPPP candidate Karamat Ullah Khan wins PK-72 election
content:
ISLAMABAD, Feb 9 (APP): Pakistan People’s Party Parliamentarian (PPPP) candidate Karamat Ullah Khan won the Khyber Pakhtunkhwa Assembly election from PK-72, Peshawar-I by securing 18,527 votes.
According to the unofficial result issued by the Returning Officer/ECP, his runner-up was an independent candidate Mehmood Khan who bagged 14,332 votes.
Overall voters’ turn-out remained 37.13 per cent.
